commit_message:
Make ovb-manage-stack role usable for upstream reproducers

Currently the ovb-manage-stack role does not have any way to
setup a non-root user and no way to dump an inventory file. This
works fine when used with the rest of quickstart, because we have
other code that does these things.

However in order to reproduce tripleo-ci OVB jobs we want to
simply provision an environment like tebroker does in those jobs.
Then we just hand that environment off to the tripleo-ci job
scripts.

This change adds two optional bits (both off by default) that will
add a non-root user and dump an inventory file.

Change-Id: I9ee4402572583d6acb7cfdbde79b4b2e41a53fdf

commit_message:
Expose a bug when create trust with roles

The test here should pass with 400 Bad Request because
that there is no valid roles in the request body.
But Keystone raise 500 error because that it doesn't
check the roles key.

Partial-Bug: #1734244
Change-Id: Ic007c8f83717aa69ecb831d460a3829d3f8f1a6d

version is bumped.

Note: my personal rationale to trigger the new release is to include
latest fixes to in-tree tempest tests. AFAIU it should be fine to
trigger a new release at any point in time.

Change-Id: I7ccbbefb1fe7e83ccc9f12710be671bd25e71bb9

commit_message:
test-log-collect.sh: Collect package and repository info on Ubuntu

The script supports collecting information for packages and
repositories for openSUSE and CentOS but not for Ubuntu so add the
appropriate commands for it. This also fixes some indentation issues.

commit_message:
Add more logging for software deployment updates

Include the server ID in existing logs, and add additional logs that will
let us know when updates to software deployments have happened and whether
they have succeeded or not. This should save considerable time
investigating in the future if there's ever any question of whether a
deployment has gone missing in Heat itself or somewhere on the target
server.

Change-Id: I33d7aee5974d03b7e41beab9fef4ad643cb0c469

commit_message:
config: Always add step conditional first for upgrade_tasks

This is required to ensure conditionals using variables set by prior
steps are not evaluated prior to these steps running.

Closes-bug: #1732888
Change-Id: I9f6d60f22ef4c057a0d5f47ac2bd4f08520faeec

commit_message:
Set ceph_use_fqdn for rdocloud

Multinode deployments on rdocloud make the hostname *.rdocloud.
This means that we need to pass an extra argument to ceph-ansible
in order to have ceph-mon configured correctly.

The actual logic for this option is implemented in the depends-on
patch.

Change-Id: Id9668b340cb97cc309bd1618a25b0936b8d54113
Depends-On: I79cb56a10b4dd60c7bb7bab40bbdc5711f61f27b

The upgrade_task that remove packages have a when clause that is

commit_message:
Handle 'false' in when statements for ansible upgrade_tasks

The upgrade_task that remove packages have a when clause that is
set from the UpgradeRemoveUnusedPackages parameter. When we write
the overcloud config and translate "tags: step" to "when: step"
we must be careful to handle these tasks otherwise we get errors.
See the bug for more info.

Change-Id: Ic10ae0f3262a93ceec6ba8d938f36c937f3b594c
Closes-Bug: 1734118

commit_message:
Stop the object-expirer service before removing swift-proxy

As discussed in the bug below, the expirer service is provided
by the swift-proxy package so it needs to be stopped at the
same time as swift-proxy and not with the other swift services

Change-Id: I01518f82cef494682b4359ba7849ba7e37ac39cc
Related-Bug: 1701501
(cherry picked from commit b3d1d45ba5cd0d608b514cca9aaa53eb6ddc45e8)

commit_message:
Implement query param schema for flavor index

GET flavor API accept query param to filter the
flavors.
This commit adds json schema to validate the valid
query parameters.

There is no change in API behaviour and additionalProperties
is kept True for backward compatibility.

Partially implements blueprint json-schema-validation-for-query-param

Change-Id: I61324ba58eddfed1445d7c70db761961e1b6a864

commit_message:
Remove the ensure_dir

The utils.file.ensure_dir is deprecated for removal in version Ocata.
ensure_tree(path, 0o755) from the oslo_utils.fileutils can be used

commit_message:
zuul: run TripleO jobs with new zuulv3 layout

Configure the layout to execute the scenario007 jobs.
Note that baremetal job will be run on stable/pike and container on
Queens and beyond.

A note has been added in comment explaining more details.

Change-Id: I61e9d316ad283076a735344635cbcb227ee0de09
Depends-On: I8f8f0ce918d83cc99792cb0554ec081d4c3bc20b

commit_message:
Add py35 gate for ironic-inspector

This patch adds py35 gate for ironic-inspector and
also adds support for inspection in python3 environment
by rolling out configuration of swift in inspector.

Change-Id: I83429a1ba79208245f6c6e1f8b4eb8a16f014868

commit_message:
Setting default log url for tempestmail

Tempestmail needs to know in which url the logs are stored.
By default it uses logs.openstack.org, however, since these jobs are
being executed in rdo-cloud and logs stored in a different server, this
set is required when the email is send point to the proper url.

Change-Id: I9ccb073da4485a1d0fc9fe6ae8cca3d36dd6f081
Depends-On: Iab9b448551d1a2ed59b47f91d5a9bcc204e0a703

commit_message:
Adding the possibility to pass the log url to tempestmail

Tempestmail is being used in other CI that don't work like the
openstack upstream ci, and logs are stored somewhere else.
This patch allows the possibility to pass --log-url option
to tempestmail script override the default log path.

Change-Id: Iab9b448551d1a2ed59b47f91d5a9bcc204e0a703

commit_message:
ironic: rework enrollment with the recent changes

* Explain resource classes and add them to post-configuration commands
* Explain inventory fields thay may not be obvious
* Mention that host aggregates won't be needed in Queens
* Add more ways to validate that ironic services run and report properly
* Small fixes here and there

Note that the complete switch to resource classes is still in progress
in Queens, so the guide still defaults to Pike-era configuration.

Change-Id: I453912dde1e660c49cd889650b19e4bb80201b0b

I think this is fine to give more information, would like to get Lance's view on this too"}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2017-05-27 11:57:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

I'm still concerned about this. Letting the user know that the token has expired means admitting that the token used to be valid, which could be useful to an attacker. I still think this would have been fine as a debug log."}, {'account_id': 5046, 'date': '2017-06-05 20:54:19.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

I would prefer to keep cases like this as opaque as possible, mainly for the reasons that Colleen has already stated.

If I see this message as an attacker, I know the the information represented by this token could very well still be valid, with the exception of the expiration. If it's a fernet token an attacker could throw resources at trying to decrypt it. By not giving out this information, we make jumping to that conclusion harder for an attacker (is the token revoked because the user no longer has a role on that project? is the token revoked because of expiration? did the user explicitly revoke this token? did they change their password? etc..)

Regardless of the specific reason for the 401, a valid user knows they have to re-authenticate. I don't think exposing this information to them would change that behavior, but it would be useful to certain attackers."}, {'account_id': 16465, 'date': '2017-06-05 21:01:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Completely agree with Lance's argumentation about decrypting Fernet tokens."}, {'account_id': 2874, 'date': '2017-06-06 04:42:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 18338, 'date': '2017-06-07 18:30:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Need to understand the use case as to why this is needed.'}, {'account_id': 5046, 'date': '2017-11-27 16:28:41.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

It's been about 6 months without an update. I'm going to abandon this to clear up some of the review queue. In the event we decide to go this direction, or a different use case is brought forward, we can re-evaluate the change."}]

commit_message:
More messages about validating token failed

If a token has expired, the response is just 'Failed to validate token'
without the specific reason about it.

Change-Id: I61d97e3acfb899adf2977c4ec3d4a30b2df18fd9

Keystone doesn't allow to delete extra properties. We can unset
their values: the same operation as to set property value to None
(according to action presented in V2), but keystone will continue
store these properties in DB and return them with None values.
This behavior significantly influences on UX, when user activelly
uses these fields to mark/unmark project (users, roles, domains),
because it leads to mess in an output of CLI or UI.

Change-Id: Idb79e422f6cf9743e37c78abdfd6a13869ef17c0
"}]
commit_message:
Added filtering of empty extra properties

Keystone doesn't allow to delete extra properties. We can unset
their values: the same operation as to set property value to None
(according to action presented in V2), but keystone will continue
store these properties in DB and return them with None values.
This behavior significantly influences on UX, when user activelly
uses these fields to mark/unmark project (users, roles, domains),
because it leads to mess in an output of CLI or UI.

This patch adds filtering of empty properties to prevent cluttering
of extra field that contains custom properties for objects.

Change-Id: Idb79e422f6cf9743e37c78abdfd6a13869ef17c0

commit_message:
Polish swift containers logging configuration

The logging directories are not used by swift, which in turn logs
to syslog. So the unnecessary bind-mounts were removed.

Furthermore, as part of the swift package which is included in the
overcloud image, there is an rsyslog rule which gets the swift logs
and persists them in /var/log/swift. Due to this and to be consistent
with the rest of the containers. A symlink was created to have the
swift logs available from /var/log/containers/swift as well. This makes
the readme indicating the change of place of the logs unnecessary, so
that was removed as well.

Closes-Bug: #1732107
Change-Id: I61610d3cb187235ac316e1c5de0a344be3ebb1e2
(cherry picked from commit 84e9425edab83578d09fa612a1e772b188a9c3db)

[{'created': '2017-06-28 16:51:08.000000000', 'message': "Convert the legacy lxc bridge to networkd

This change implements the lxcbr0 interface in systemd-networkd. This is
being done to simplify how this bridge is setup and to unify it's
management across distros. The change removes all of the old dnsmasq
process and cleans up variables, templates, and files that are no longer
needed.

commit_message:
Convert the legacy lxc bridge to networkd

This change implements the lxcbr0 interface in systemd-networkd. This is
being done to simplify how this bridge is setup and to unify it's
management across distros. The change removes all of the old dnsmasq
process and cleans up variables, templates, and files that are no longer
needed.

New tests have been added to create a container and ping an external
address in an effort to ensure the container build and host setup
process works as expected.

Change-Id: Ib2b9062b8290c9b3bccb1ae64806f86c818ad8b1
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Remove use_neutron option

Nova network has been fully removed from the OpenStack codebase.
As such, all instances of switches on use_neutron should be removed,
as the functionality will never be meaningful.

Change-Id: I2eb338ba53d51c62c88bbbfd145462030596da74
Depends-On: Ib9d87dd339d637b69fb27315d92228cbc523c8eb
Closes-Bug: #1734615

commit_message:
Remove required-projects from post docs jobs

The docs job is a final job, we cannot add required-projects here.

Remove them and the job, it's part of the publish template that is used.

Note that currently no post jobs are run due to the wrong setup. This
change breaks the post job temporarily but allows the other post jobs to
run while work is ongoing on the post docs job.

Change-Id: I373f870b47b69da7b034de2b7c4912bbd4a619aa

messages:
[{'account_id': 20190, 'date': '2017-11-23 09:28:30.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 5689, 'date': '2017-11-27 08:32:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

nice catch. 409 is always state conflict.'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-23 09:28:30.000000000', 'message': 'Change Conflict's error message

Conflict exception's error message is sometimes misleading,
e.g.,

<class 'tempest.lib.exceptions.Conflict'>,
An object with that identifier already exists
Details: {u'message':
            u'Unable to complete operation on subnet
              98575cac-0a2f-4214-8dea-50c62d31e736:
            One or more ports have an IP allocation from this subnet.',
            u'type': u'SubnetInUse', u'detail': u''}

according to https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.8,
"The 409 (Conflict) status code indicates that the request could not
be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the target
resource", so this is to change the error message to
"Conflict with state of target resource".

Change-Id: Icc118ec67f05cc7640e2b5f12162547ae5c3dae5
'}]
commit_message:
Change Conflict's error message

Conflict exception's error message is sometimes misleading,
e.g.,

<class 'tempest.lib.exceptions.Conflict'>,
An object with that identifier already exists
Details: {u'message':
            u'Unable to complete operation on subnet
              98575cac-0a2f-4214-8dea-50c62d31e736:
            One or more ports have an IP allocation from this subnet.',
            u'type': u'SubnetInUse', u'detail': u''}

according to https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.8,
"The 409 (Conflict) status code indicates that the request could not
be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the target
resource", so this is to change the error message to
"Conflict with state of target resource".

Change-Id: Icc118ec67f05cc7640e2b5f12162547ae5c3dae5

commit_message:
Include 'queens' as target version for upgrade.

The target_upgrade_version is not queens, so
without this change no upgrade job in master
will run a complete upgrade as the overcloud
deploy command to upgrade is not being run.

Change-Id: I8f4cfc4596c6a48a2526379e8a11aefad97c290e
Depends-On: Id53b609ff6f31e1da96598c180151239be287242
Closes-Bug: #1728917

commit_message:
Use 'PermitRootLogin 'without-password''

Since https://review.openstack.org/#/c/518013/7 merged we can now set
the value of security_sshd_permit_root_login to be 'without-password',
we should do this in favour of 'yes'.

Change-Id: I624d29752fca5a8cbf4cab455f32f0116b99ff82

commit_message:
Performance oriented unit test for HMT

Create a project tree, then call for every project:
  - resource_api.list_projects_in_subtree()
  - resource_api.list_project_parents()

commit_message:
Allow the user to run ansible update on all nodes

Do not limit the nodes to update to the --nodes option
will allow the user to run the update on all nodes
with simply:

openstack overcloud update stack

Change-Id: I912e3881b44d4fbf78b6679deb23eb0b5f9a228d
(cherry picked from commit 73dce75602feac411c1546ea828b64d7157d0b5a)

I don't get it.  The variables are defined and run only at step3.  The block has the step3 tag, which is inherited to all tasks as is the when conditional.  So the block shouldn't run at any other step.  If so, this is a different issue.

Checking what is downloaded, ie how those snippets are actually rendered should provide more intel."}, {'account_id': 18851, 'date': '2017-11-23 20:59:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

 > Checking what is downloaded, ie how those snippets are actually
 > rendered should provide more intel.

I pasted the playbooks from my system here: http://paste.openstack.org/show/627263/

It looks that we run the upgrade playbook for step 0-5:

- hosts: overcloud
  tasks:
    - include: upgrade_steps_tasks.yaml
      with_sequence: start=0 end=5
      loop_control:
        loop_var: step

So in case of step=0 for instance the tasks for registering the os_net_config_need_upgrade and os_net_config_has_config are skipped because the step doesn't match the when conditional:

- name: Check for os-net-config upgrade
  register: os_net_config_need_upgrade
  shell: yum check-upgrade | awk '/os-net-config/{print}'
  tags: step3
  when: step|int == 3
- ignore_errors: true
  name: Check that os-net-config has configuration
  register: os_net_config_has_config
  shell: test -s /etc/os-net-config/config.json
  tags: step3
  when: step|int == 3

but then Ansible tries to evaluate them to determine the conditional result for:

- block:
  - name: Upgrade os-net-config
    yum: name=os-net-config state=latest
  - changed_when: os_net_config_upgrade.rc == 2
    command: os-net-config --no-activate -c /etc/os-net-config/config.json -v --detailed-exit-codes
    failed_when: os_net_config_upgrade.rc not in [0,2]
    name: take new os-net-config parameters into account now
    register: os_net_config_upgrade
  tags: step3
  when:
  - os_net_config_need_upgrade.stdout and os_net_config_has_config.rc == 0
  - step|int == 3

Note the when conditional contains step|int == 3 and atributes of the os_net_config* vars which are undefined as they were skipped previously."}, {'account_id': 8297, 'date': '2017-11-23 21:37:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

So this is what is rendered:


- ignore_error: true
  name: Check for os-net-config upgrade
  register: os_net_config_need_upgrade
  shell: yum check-upgrade | grep os-net-config
  tags: step3
  when: step|int == 3
- ignore_error: true
  name: Check that os-net-config has configuration
  register: os_net_config_has_config
  shell: test -s /etc/os-net-config/config.json
  tags: step3
  when: step|int == 3
- block:
  - name: Upgrade os-net-config
    yum: name=os-net-config state=latest
  - changed_when: os_net_config_upgrade.rc == 2
    command: os-net-config --no-activate -c /etc/os-net-config/config.json -v --detailed-exit-codes
    failed_when: os_net_config_upgrade.rc not in [0,2]
    name: take new os-net-config parameters into account now
    register: os_net_config_upgrade
  tags: step3
  when:
  - not os_net_config_need_upgrade.stdout and os_net_config_has_config.rc == 0
  - step|int == 3


(complete rendition there [1])

And this is the problem.  When we use heat during normal upgrade we use the tags to exclude/include ansible tasks.  That means that the conditional is not executed at all when we use:

   ansible-playbook ... -t stepN

    with N != 3

and the playbook works correctly.

For non-controller we use a different idiom where we iterate over the tasks by setting an variable.  The equivalent run is

    ansible-playbook -e step=3 ...

there, the when statement *is* evaluated no matter what.

So while the ansible register definition will be executed only when step == 3, the block conditional will be executed for all steps, failing when step != 3 with undef stdout/rc property.

Now that it's crystal clear (for me), let's think about the best solution.

[1] https://ptpb.pw/LEdP/text"}, {'account_id': 8449, 'date': '2017-11-24 09:23:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

commit_message:
Ensure os-net-config conditional for upgrade doesn’t fail.

When using grep the check will fail if no upgrade is available.  This
has the side effect of not registering the variable and the check
later on will fail as “.stdout” property is not defined.

Using awk doesn’t have this side effect and will return empty stdout
without error in case of error.

Change-Id: I9d9bb3b625c2f0fb5f4a2c98bd3bf903f4bec176
Closes-Bug: #1733924

commit_message:
Finish deprecation of pull_source

In change I0b0b8728b7752bdd4680a5a2bbf664f94f7d56d9 the --pull-source
argument was deprecated in favour of a --namespace which includes the
source registry.

This change makes the default namespace docker.io/tripleoupstream to
be consistent with the default that the CLI uses. Tests now do not use
pull_source so that proper testing of fully qualified namespace
arguments is done.

Change-Id: Icd29f0e75c3edadfb008056af774e283200002b0
Related-Bug: #1708303

commit_message:
Quota limits

Quotas are scattered across OpenStack services.
Each service defines own models and APIs for managing limits.
Because of that, there are several problems:
 - Name of the resources and resource-service mapping  are hardcoded.
 - There is no centralized quota management for OpenStack projects.
 - Cinder, Nova and Neutron support hierarchical quotas
   in different ways.
There should be a single point of managing quotas in OpenStack.
Keystone looks like a right place to store quotas limits because
Keystone stores projects and limits are belong to projects.

Change-Id: I9661e4e8ecca454d456d716475868f632d0130d1

commit_message:
Change PermitRootLogin to allow alternate options

PermitRootLogin can be 'yes', 'no', 'without-password',
'prohibit-password' or 'forced-commands-only'.
This patch changes the functionality to ensure that
security_sshd_permit_root_login is one of the above settings - if so, it
will use that value.

Due to the way Ansible handles "no" and "yes", we have to check if the
value is "False" (string equivalent for boolean no), and if so output
"no", otherwise output the string (which would be one of the above
options).

Previously, we could only set this value to 'no'.

Change-Id: I5ee5ff6abc4578d17d4b23d8a2fa1648508ceeed
(cherry picked from commit f32cb3c0817441e3ba907c6481963bdd03c869cd)

commit_message:
Fix dumps_log playbook

Currently, execution openstack.sh in the dumps_log is not performed
causing some variable in the dumps_log.sh to be empty.  Consequently,
any openstack-related logs are not captured at the end of the gate.
This patch set should fix the path issue of the openstack.sh.

Change-Id: I1d8f5733d49476e80c7fa1399f46bcd6c45198c0

commit_message:
Switch baremetal nics/ports tests over

Moved baremetal port tests to a separate file and
updated them to utilize the new testing method.

Additionally, normalized the output of the port lists as
noise is introduced that is not needed.

Change-Id: I60492cca893e823cb2f9937405c75e23cc42807d

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-09-25 19:40:55.000000000', 'message': 'Ignore errors in OS::stack_id output

If a provider stack contained an OS::stack_id output and there was an error
in the output, we would raise TemplateOutputError when trying to calculate
the reference ID of the facade resource. Since we do that in many API
calls, such an error could render the stack effectively unusable.

If we encounter such an error, log it and fall back to the default
reference ID.

Change-Id: I1bc921fe74c54eb0999541ef36afc42b9c19e9bc
Partial-Bug: #1712280
Related-Bug: #1719333
'}]
commit_message:
Ignore errors in OS::stack_id output

If a provider stack contained an OS::stack_id output and there was an error
in the output, we would raise TemplateOutputError when trying to calculate
the reference ID of the facade resource. Since we do that in many API
calls, such an error could render the stack effectively unusable.

If we encounter such an error, log it and fall back to the default
reference ID.

Change-Id: I1bc921fe74c54eb0999541ef36afc42b9c19e9bc
Partial-Bug: #1712280
Related-Bug: #1719333

commit_message:
Remove required-jobs from final docs job

We cannot modify the final job, remove the required-jobs. This will
break the publishing - but right now *no* post job runs for these and
that's even worse.

We would need to remove the required-project lines from check and gate
as well but if we do this, they fail completely and thus repos using
this cannot merge anything. Let's do this later once the jobs are
changed to not use tox - see topic:updated-pti.

Change-Id: I5bc1ac2816c1a7bba425d06db9e8bb8bdf025c32

commit_message:
Add OpenShift gates

This commit adds gates that test Kuryr with OpenShift. Complex gates
that test with both OpenShift and CNI daemon enabled are added to
experimental queue only.

Partial-Implements: blueprint enhance-upstream-gates

Change-Id: I4162b31e6af3ca4b527dc5eb17e53be46e013daf

commit_message:
Integrate OVO in helpers

I0d592bae452876b24c28ca4cc4bf6392b5ab6493 integrated ovo with
neutrons allocation models. OVO can be further integrated in the
helpers file.

This will make the addition of QinQ networks easier because it
refactors the type_vlan code and that logic now uses OVO. Rather
than reverting those changes, consumers of this file should adopt
OVO.

The following projects use helpers.SegmentTypeDriver with a model
that is not an OVO and will be effected by this change:
networking-avaya
networking-bagpipe
networking-h3c

Partial-Bug: #1705719
Change-Id: I4e11cbf22f9fbf0235e68d6eb84ee68a116b0398
Partially-Implements: blueprint adopt-oslo-versioned-objects-for-db

While writing the QinQ driver, the logic for syncing vlan
allocations was somewhat duplicated. This refactors the function
to add conditional cases for it to be compatibile for both drivers.

The QinQ driver adds another layer of keys so instead of set
operations we need to use dictionary operations and also
another layer of nesting is needed for for loops to act on those
values.

commit_message:
Refactor type_vlan for QinQ compatibility

While writing the QinQ driver, the logic for syncing vlan
allocations was somewhat duplicated. This commit refactors
it enough so it can be used by both drivers.

The QinQ driver adds another layer of keys so instead of set
operations we need to use dictionary operations and also
another layer of nesting is needed for for loops to act on those
values.

Partial-Bug: #1705719

Change-Id: Ice309b12ce2693627d8c9d69265fddf195c51161

Hi Trevor,

Can you please file a separate RFE for this independent of https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1604222 .

VLAN transparency for OVS depends on QinQ support in the vswitch, but it doesn't have anything to do with this type driver. This type driver is about putting QinQ packets on the wire.

VLAN transparency in OVS will only depend on QinQ internally to avoid destroying the VLANs that are coming out of VM interfaces as they are tagged internally by the integration bridge.

I don't want the two to get confused because this driver doesn't bring us any closer to OVS agent VLAN transparency."}, {'account_id': 20378, 'date': '2017-07-21 14:44:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 48:

> Hi Trevor,
 > 
 > Can you please file a separate RFE for this independent of
 > https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1604222 .
 > 
 > VLAN transparency for OVS depends on QinQ support in the vswitch,
 > but it doesn't have anything to do with this type driver. This type
 > driver is about putting QinQ packets on the wire.
 > 
 > VLAN transparency in OVS will only depend on QinQ internally to
 > avoid destroying the VLANs that are coming out of VM interfaces as
 > they are tagged internally by the integration bridge.
 > 
 > I don't want the two to get confused because this driver doesn't

"}, {'created': '2017-04-03 21:42:38.000000000', 'message': 'WIP: Add QinQ network type driver

This patch aims to add a QinQ network type driver by modifying
the existing segment table and adding an allocation table.

type_qinq.py copies some logic from type_vlan.py and modifies it
to fit the needs of QinQ segments.

A user can confgiure the network with the following format:
    <physical_network>:<s_tag>:<c_tag_min>:<c_tag_max>

If a user specifies the same <physical_network>:<s_tag> pair again,
the c-tags for the matching record will be overwritten.

Related-Bug: #1604222
Change-Id: I46c74dcc0d18d9a6cde930c1f3e2408c0c699557
'}, {'created': '2017-04-04 16:47:05.000000000', 'message': 'Add QinQ network type driver

This patch aims to add a QinQ network type driver by modifying
the existing segment table and adding an allocation table.

type_qinq.py copies some logic from type_vlan.py and modifies it

commit_message:
Add QinQ network type driver

NOTE: This patch depends on a refactor so if you can't find
a function definition, check the depends-on link here:
    Ice309b12ce2693627d8c9d69265fddf195c51161

This patch aims to add a QinQ network type driver by adding an
allocation table for QinQ.

type_qinq.py copied some logic from type_vlan.py so this caused a
refactor into helpers.py type_qinq.py  uses/modifies it to fit the
needs of QinQ segments.

A user can confgiure the network with the following format:
    <physical_network>:<s_tag>:<c_tag_min>:<c_tag_max>

When a user creates a network with the configured s_tag
specified as the provider-segment, it will allocate the
entire c_tag range configured for that s_tag.

Closes-Bug: #1705719
Change-Id: I46c74dcc0d18d9a6cde930c1f3e2408c0c699557

commit_message:
Add network_map entry to dynamic inventory

This gives a list of all the networks with all the relevant information
about them, which makes it easier to consume via ansible.

One would get the name of the network, the current IP, and the VIP
information for each network (with an empty list if no VIPs exist for
this network).

bp ipsec
Change-Id: I79b40e97095edb3ee165f535ec2e0254cc8baf8e

commit_message:
Add a configuration option for the default resource class

If no resource class is provided in a creation request, the value of
the new ``default_resource_class`` configuration option is used.

While this feature is implemented on the API level, it's not a part of
the API contract, so it's not covered by a microversion. It's particularly
important, because it allows this change to apply even to requests
using an old API version, thus making these versions usable after
the mandatory switch to resource classes in nova.

Change-Id: I58232d9c92d6ffca49d334e5fb7078bce19f1cb4
Closes-Bug: #1732190

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: If695142020e9d877163f40a10f360b9dce264bb3

Don't use oslo context get_logging_values

get_logging_values has been changed recently to not pass the token
anymore, call to_dict as expected.

Change-Id: I3a7f1293a4d0082274af270f86b5c732d898f8bc
Closes-Bug: #1733345

commit_message:
Parse pcs auth output with all pcs versions

Newer pcs versions don't print "Debug Output" messages anymore
but use "Debug Stdout". Since the pcs cluster auth functions
parse that output, let's make sure we match both strings.

Change-Id: I32a7a9fa4b896871929fcae847bba3481df5b517
Closes-Bug: #1718186
Partial-Bug: #1733372
(cherry picked from commit a2e9675cda2e9152569ce4ab0f69484c03fc7c93)

commit_message:
Allow the haproxy configuration to run with limited groups

The haproxy config we have makes a couple assumptions about groups being
present. this change simply improves our existing config so that it
works should a deployer omit common groups within a deployment.

Change-Id: Iae3798c98c250e959f660603263405aa88a4e1a1
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Collect OVS databases in tempest logs

When tempest jobs run, we're not collecting openvswitch databases
and sometimes they're useful for debugging purposes since they
contain all the transactions that have happened during the run.

Co-Authored-By: Miguel Angel Ajo <majopela@redhat.com>
Change-Id: Ie06d1a20cb0bb25fa1e0cd4352cf27c1dcf3d01c
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>

[{'created': '2017-11-15 02:29:45.000000000', 'message': 'Fix the host_get_all_by_queries() method

Current logic misjudges that a ComputeHost object does not have an
attribute which is specified in a query if the value of the attribute
is 0 or False. This patch fixes the logic.

Change-Id: I9143f11dd022fe3f683c0f3a2a87c3f5562461d8
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the host_get_all_by_queries() method

Current logic misjudges that a ComputeHost object does not have an
attribute which is specified in a query if the value of the attribute
is 0 or False. This patch fixes the logic.

Change-Id: I9143f11dd022fe3f683c0f3a2a87c3f5562461d8

commit_message:
Use addClassResourceCleanup to cleanup floatingips

This is to use addClassResourceCleanup for the cleanup of floatingips,
so the cleanup in resource_cleanup can be removed.

Change-Id: If8fdf2278b1b70f94816c4fe1a78566c8ac999a5

commit_message:
Collect logs to a subfolder

The logs and ara report generated by zuul are
overwriting some of our log content, so this
patch puts our logs into a subfolder instead.

Change-Id: I28712418fb6db4857dc9f74b2ee8b2fbeb651853
(cherry picked from commit 5868c615a45d95699a2da707d1832dc37c120044)

commit_message:
Install python-apt before hooks run

Previously this charm had relied on python-apt being installed by
the principle. As charms migrate to py3 this is no longer a safe
assumption and actually never was. This change ensures that
python-apt is installed before immediatly. This follows the same
pattern

Change-Id: I21ca95a9f2e410a52a7b64c99fad85749d52473a

[{'created': '2017-11-06 15:07:42.000000000', 'message': "Change PermitRootLogin to be a string

PermitRootLogin can be 'yes', 'no' or 'without-password' this patch
changes the security_sshd_permit_root_login option to allow this to
be a string rather than a boolean value.

commit_message:
Change PermitRootLogin to allow alternate options

PermitRootLogin can be 'yes', 'no', 'without-password',
'prohibit-password' or 'forced-commands-only'.
This patch changes the functionality to ensure that
security_sshd_permit_root_login is one of the above settings - if so, it
will use that value.

Due to the way Ansible handles "no" and "yes", we have to check if the
value is "False" (string equivalent for boolean no), and if so output
"no", otherwise output the string (which would be one of the above
options).

Previously, we could only set this value to 'no'.

Change-Id: I5ee5ff6abc4578d17d4b23d8a2fa1648508ceeed

Use 'find' to replace the list method when search volume.

Fix error when "zun run --mount=<volume-name>" that could
not find the volume.

commit_message:
Initialize ovn_client properly when mech_driver object is reused

Functional tests currently reuse the mech_driver object and
TestOVNFunctionalBase class calls post_fork_initialize() method.
This forces the IDL connections to be renewed but old ovn_client
object still holds the references to the old connections which
produces NotConnectedError exceptions in ovsdbapp.

This patch fixes it by resetting the ovn_client instance in the
mechanism driver in the post_fork_initialize() method.

Closes-Bug: #1733399

Change-Id: I85fc8c54c0bda4bdfc76f9f74ec40260d998b756
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>

commit_message:
libvirt check: use unqualified hostname

Nova will always use an unqualified host name for an instance's
compute node. If monasca-agent is configured to use a compute
node's fully qualified host name for metrics and that gets used for
looking up the instances running on that node, Nova will return
zero results. This commit fixes this problem by always reducing
the the host name to its first component.

Change-Id: Ie29cb2dc305c8b2d4c551d1512e0e755f9e38cb6
Story: 2001251
Task: 5781
(cherry picked from commit 48729136a7a01b07624b702f0b59af3c69e3fcca)

commit_message:
Don't change directory while running init-runonce

Currently init-runonce script changes directory to the
script's base directory (/usr/...) before doing anything else.
This unnecessarily _forces_ a non-root user to use sudo for
running this script thereby raising privileges for code which
doesn't want it. Also downloading temporary stuff in places like
/usr... seems not a good choice.

Hence deleting the said code part and letting the deployer work
comfortably from any directory.

Made documentation changes accordingly.

Change-Id: Ib3c7ed97aa5f53c115b6337aaf572b5fdc7a71f3
Closes-Bug: #1732963

commit_message:
Add DeployIdentifier to Nova discover hosts container

Resolves an issue during scale out where the Nova init
container that runs discover hosts wasn't executing on a Heat
stack update if the container name and configs all stayed the same.

Change-Id: Ie2ecd3dbddb1cf3ee5bba6f7b33e11bc9b6b8b4e
Closes-bug: 1733966

subject: Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes
messages: [{'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2017-11-17 09:07:03.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 6618, 'date': '2017-11-20 16:01:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nThanks.'}, {'account_id': 9796, 'date': '2017-11-27 04:44:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-17 09:07:03.000000000', 'message': "Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: Idc3bf6f4d620e1b7b10600dc28d46dd2e7d0d9e8

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: Idc3bf6f4d620e1b7b10600dc28d46dd2e7d0d9e8

commit_message:
Use the proper link name for the newton dlrn variable

The previous fix used the wrong "current-tripleo" link name. However for
newton we still use the legacy "current-passed-ci" link on the DLRN
server.

Also fix "passed-ci" to "current-passed-ci" in the list of known dlrn
hashes.

Change-Id: I70afa68fbc1d941b128fadcc1d25b4d3e4a88d8b
Closes-Bug: #1733598

commit_message:
Remove use_neutron from sahara config

Nova network has been fully removed from the OpenStack codebase.
As such, all instances of switches on use_neutron should be removed,
as the functionality will never be meaningful.

Change-Id: I6af9af897b5a4416082307e01dca951c9b7026ad
Depends-On: Ib9d87dd339d637b69fb27315d92228cbc523c8eb

commit_message:
Configure glance ceph during upgrade and genconfig

Previously the glance ceph backend was only being configured during
the deploy and reconfigure commands. This change ensures that it is
configured during the upgrade and genconfig commands as well.

Some of the related host/group selection logic has been cleaned up,
as it was a little tautolgous.

Change-Id: Ibfc2bfaaf2e24fb3a0697925e7723794046787fa
Closes-Bug: #1728060

commit_message:
Temporary work around a docker issue

Docker daemon responses 500 if calling exec_resize on an non-existing
exec instance. This patch work around the issue until it is fixed
in Docker side.

See: https://github.com/moby/moby/issues/35561

Change-Id: I1372d22eaae0b1fa42b91873f9b749a275478b71
Related-Bug: #1732498

commit_message:
Disable glance file backend with external Ceph

When using external Ceph cluster, glance_api container is only running
on one controller instead of running on all of them.

But when an external Ceph cluster is used, enable_ceph is false so
glance_backend_file is true

Using "not glance_backend_ceph | bool" instead of "not enable_ceph |
bool" should be enough.

Change-Id: I191e5ea7a0d51b0e19ed58a819c3ade5070f623d
Closes-Bug: #1722905

commit_message:
Remove deprecated version dependencies in quickstart

Mitaka and newton are deprecated and no longer maintained
by OpenStack comunity.

Users can check specific documentation for old releases.

Change-Id: I43fd1d40bc2f094fee4c1547879f798a92593df4

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html

Change-Id: I58b359848331f9d6621f6ce3f67665b14610027a

commit_message:
Generate stestr.conf

When run functional tests, a warning was raised:

UserWarning: No .stestr.conf file found in the CWD. Please create one
to to replace the .testr.conf. [1]

This patch creates a .stestr.conf file but keep .testr.conf. Will
remove it & its usage when testrepository is completely replaced by
stestr. OpenStack has a long-term plan for this [2].

[1] http://logs.openstack.org/67/521567/1/check/openstack-tox-py35/77ed34b/job-output.txt.gz#_2017-11-20_16_11_00_990062
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/491075/

Change-Id: I1a8fb9de958ba8f876097b30530b6f55e59350fc

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: Ic580bc42c7f2334a09666daf9bcb0fee9a517b97

commit_message:
Add a validation to create lease API

The create lease API doesn't check request body has required parameters
or not. If a request doesn't have required parameters, the API returns
500 Internal Server.

This patch adds a validation method to check whether a request body has
required parameters, start_time, end_time and lease name.

Change-Id: Ibde14d3821b858db962228bf90294efb821cc462
Closes-Bug: #1710809

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html

commit_message:
Cleanup nova cell configuration before config it

Some old configuration(such as, LOG_COLOR config) will remain
if we don't cleanup.

So, we should cleanup the configuration before we config it.

Change-Id: I7aff609dadf3acba13a36894614b35005f51280d

commit_message:
Align tox_install.sh with other projects

The tox_install.sh here behaves a bit differently than the others, which
is causing some problems when trying to rework some of the shared gate jobs.

Align it to the form used in other repos.

Change-Id: I3d2b391fba9be6290eb245924014134fbdde717a

It seems it is common to have subnetpool prefixes larger than the subnet cidr. In particular, there is a scenario to have a shared pool across tenants and each tenant subnet allocated a portion of the ip network from the pool. commit_message:
Handle shared network senario

Create a network that shared by all tenants. Create container from shared
network in different tenants. The container will fail with docker internal
error.

Reproduce
=========
$ source /opt/stack/devstack/openrc admin admin
$ openstack network create --share test
$ openstack subnet create --subnet-range 10.2.0.0/24 --network test testsubnet

$ zun run --net network=test nginx

| status_reason | Docker internal error: 500 Server Error: Internal Server
Error ("IpamDriver.RequestPool: Another pool with same cidr exist. ipam and
network options not used to pass pool name").

This bug needs to the depends-on patch in kuryr-libnetwork.

commit_message:
Allow custom FQDNs for over/under-clouds endpoints

Allow to customize t-h-t 'Cloud*' params for overcloud and undercloud.

Move defaults to the common role, and make undercloud names to follow the
overcloud names by default, yet allowing to diverge. F.e. RDOcloud uses an
'rdocloud' domain, therefore some DNS things might be failing
with the 'localdomain' hardcoded values.

Change the subdomains placement order from 'overcloud.storage.localdomain' to
'storage.overcloud.localdomain'. That allows to consistently propagate changes
to the overcloud/undercloud endpoints' names based on a single change provided
for undercloud_domain or overcloud_domain, e.g:
 - storage.overcloud.localdomain
 - storage.undercloud.customdomain

Split common defaults' roles vars into generic and networking related.

Depends-on: Iad63142b241f9f7f0bbef68473f18b69f36daf76

Related-bug: #1698349
Closes-bug: #1733873

Change-Id: Ie83f5668ab3947396ac14e4375d2a50c3aed0657
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

[{'created': '2017-11-03 17:45:03.000000000', 'message': 'Remove glusterfs-native job from check queue

In the manila community meeting it was resolved [1]
to remove unmaintained drivers from the check queue
to avoid waste of infrastructure resources and to
remove "red noise" from the gerrit review pages.

Do so for the glusterfs-native driver.  Leave the
job defined as it is run in the experimental queue
and in devstack-glusterfs-plugin.

[1[ http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-meeting-alt/%23openstack-meeting-alt.2017-11-02.log.html#t2017-11-02T15:26:17

Change-Id: I87f15ee7f73a8b4a16ae0549d0f2fae4b4c23ec2
'}]
commit_message:
Remove glusterfs-native job from check queue

In the manila community meeting it was resolved [1]
to remove unmaintained drivers from the check queue
to avoid waste of infrastructure resources and to
remove "red noise" from the gerrit review pages.

Do so for the glusterfs-native driver.  Leave the
job defined as it is run in the experimental queue
and in devstack-glusterfs-plugin.

[1[ http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-meeting-alt/%23openstack-meeting-alt.2017-11-02.log.html#t2017-11-02T15:26:17

Change-Id: I87f15ee7f73a8b4a16ae0549d0f2fae4b4c23ec2

Add __all__ to __init__ for service clients

Make it easier to consume the service clients by defining
__alll__ in the __init__ of v1 v2 and admin service clients.

LBaaS spec

Implement support for Load Balancer as a Service for both L4 (LBaaS v2)
and L7 (Octavia) load balancing.

commit_message:
remove failing tripleo upgrade jobs from upstream

Remove the upgrade jobs from upstream and move them
to rdo software factory to be brought back into a
working condition.  These jobs can be readded to
upstream once they are working consistently and
running within the required timeouts.

Depends-On: I3057a5bb803d195abaf959759ad34f58a81760ed
Change-Id: I1b13c4a804816a74040f36ac0882fc6dc944466c

commit_message:
Fix usage of method ensure_dir

This patch is for stopping using ensure_dir in device_driver, as
the neutron.common.utils.ensure_dir is deprecated for removal, also
ensure_tree(path, 0o755) from oslo_utils.fileutils is suggested to be
used to create a directory.

Co-Authored-By: Cao Xuan Hoang <hoangcx@vn.fujitsu.com>
Change-Id: Ic9b4b86e65052c06c33c8628bb0c6700cdfd875b

commit_message:
Enable some off-by-default checks

Some of available checks are disabled by default,
like:[H106] Don’t put vim configuration in source
files;[H203] Use assertIs(Not)None to check for None;
[H904] Delay string interpolations at logging calls

Change-Id: Ic43e8b77cd6a700f3b71e89d6017f11a742fe87f

commit_message:
Fix trends in case of failures in contexts

In case when the context fails, there is no start_time timeframe in
workload and we should cover this case and do not fail with the next
error:

  TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for *: 'NoneType' and 'int'

Closes-Bug: #1732193
Change-Id: I95e96bb98fe473e8c0ea910021966ceb203f35cd
(cherry picked from commit af2b146d243371fdff28b146fb85c5027b79aef4)

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 25695, 'date': '2017-11-22 03:15:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Published edit on patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 23186, 'date': '2017-11-22 07:03:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)

> (1 comment)

@Ghanshyam

Neutron's policy enforcement is probably the most complicated among all the OpenStack services. We need policy in code to be done for Neutron because it's basically impossible to understand unless you really study it. Here's an introduction to Neutron policy enforcement docs: https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/b293b59b814d0abb3c6d318717e9196ae502c097/doc/source/contributor/internals/policy.rst#id11

Which means that Patrole can't really achieve stable tests until policy in code is done Neutron side."}, {'account_id': 23186, 'date': '2017-11-22 07:04:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

I'll have to pull this down locally to verify this is working as intended. Code-wise looks good though."}, {'account_id': 23186, 'date': '2017-11-22 20:02:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

-1 for inline comment.

I don't think that get_router:ha is enforced anywhere in Neutron, but I could be wrong. 

After testing this, I can't say for sure whether 'get_router:ha' is in fact enforced; I can only see 'get_router' being enforced. That being said, I'm OK with merging this. Patrole tests I've said aren't guaranteed to be stable until a 1.0 release."}, {'account_id': 25695, 'date': '2017-11-23 03:10:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Published edit on patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 23186, 'date': '2017-11-23 04:13:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 25571, 'date': '2017-11-24 04:15:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 8556, 'date': '2017-11-25 16:09:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

yea neutron policy not in code but soft -1 to remove the wrong link in commit msg.'}, {'account_id': 8556, 'date': '2017-11-25 16:10:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Commit message was updated.'}, {'account_id': 8556, 'date': '2017-11-25 16:12:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2

just fixed nit in commit msg.'}, {'account_id': 23186, 'date': '2017-11-25 20:21:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

Speaking of which, shouldn't this have its own bug beyond helping to improve test coverage?  It seems like you found an important bug in the way we were testing that reveals that a number of our tests were just written wrong and passing only because we were not comparing dictionaries correctly."}, {'account_id': 23512, 'date': '2017-11-22 11:15:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

As I understand, the tests had been comparing to wrong specs. To make the tests pass I had not only collapse the expected values, but have the dicts' values corrected, too.

For example.

See line 2049 of original file for example, the description of the group was wrong, maybe copy-pasted from somewhere. 

The line 2623 is more interesting, it shows that the value used by in the assert was the top-level key of expected dict. The key 'preserve-metadata' of internal dict had to be written with underscore.

And so on.

commit_message:
Compare API call body in assertions with respect to values

FakeClient.assert_called() compares dictionaries of actual and body 
in a wrong way. It takes into account only top-level keys of the dict,
leaving behind everything else.

Changes to the test_shell.py file fix tests which had wrong expected
values. Before this change expected values were not used properly,
that's why the tests were passing.

Closes-Bug: #1734115

Change-Id: Ib863c60a4698cbae01654bd8eea159b04d531569

commit_message:
Utilize requests lib for Huawei storage connection

For the latest Python 2.7 release, urllib uses the SSL certification
while launching URL connection by default, which causes Huawei driver
failed to connect backend storage because it doesn't support SSL
certification.
This patch fixes this issue by updating Huawei driver logic to use
requests lib for Huawei storage connection, and specifying no use of
SSL certification.

Change-Id: Ia761819a352163176d353f61682cf47a1f429966
Closes-Bug: #1733451

[{'created': '2017-11-24 07:29:49.000000000', 'message': "Do not implement reload for novnc/spice service

The nova-novncproxy and nova-spicehtml5proxy services do
not support using a HUP signal to reload, so they need to
be restarted instead.

This patch ensures that these services are restarted, and
also fixes a bug that hasn't been noticed before where if
the Placement API and other nova services are implemented
on the same host/container then the other services would
not be restarted. It would play out like this:

- The first task asks to reload all nova services execute
  against all nova hosts, except those running the placement
  api. This results in only the compute hosts getting the
  reload.

  restart. This leaves out all the other nova services
  which are on the same host.

commit_message:
Do not implement reload for novnc/spice service

The nova-novncproxy and nova-spicehtml5proxy services do
not support using a HUP signal to reload, so they need to
be restarted instead.

This patch ensures that these services are restarted, and
also fixes a bug that hasn't been noticed before where if
the Placement API and other nova services are implemented
on the same host/container then the other services would
not be restarted. It would play out like this:

- The first task asks to reload all nova services execute
  against all nova hosts, except those running the placement
  api. This results in only the compute hosts getting the
  reload.

- The second task only asks the nova placement API to
  restart. This leaves out all the other nova services
  which are on the same host.

Change-Id: Id4b9caa1cdfd0f53023548c4ede5d497d64c873d
Needed-By: I36e2200e2ca43d87208d2c4edb17b98654bb121e
(cherry picked from commit fe9a338b13411ca0f969dd9e71f6cfc309162c44)

commit_message:
Collect logs to a subfolder

The logs and ara report generated by zuul are
overwriting some of our log content, so this
patch puts our logs into a subfolder instead.

commit_message:
Use tests repo for all lint tests

The lint tests are inconsistent and often timing out due to
the implementation not using the cached repositories in the
same way as the tests repo's lint tests.

It'll be simpler to maintain if all lint tests worked the
same way.

Depends-On: I8bea90082dbde7de49c5e2e86d298c017b16591d
Change-Id: I4a5f6fe69e2d421846999c7cbd949504be77f23d

commit_message:
Collect logs to a subfolder

The logs and ara report generated by zuul are
overwriting some of our log content, so this
patch puts our logs into a subfolder instead.

Change-Id: I28712418fb6db4857dc9f74b2ee8b2fbeb651853

commit_message:
Add a background tcpdump on br-ex for ARP and ICMPv4/v6

Some tests are failing on the gate because the FIP's can't be
reached. This patch adds a tcpdump so that we can better debug this
or similar conditions in the future.

Change-Id: Icf2d18b65dd61ded6c368ecbb75c2fb0ae8c750a

[{'created': '2017-11-22 09:26:55.000000000', 'message': "Fix undercloud containers images prepare

Images for containerized underclouds can be parametrized differently
as for overcloud deployments. For example, undercloud may fetch images
from a promotion pipeline, while overcloud may consume those from the
local registry hosted undercloud.

Align the containerized undercloud case with the recent changes docker registry
host, namespace and tag defaults. Consumed these from the common defaults, yet
allowing to diverge.

Fix conditions for undercloud-deploy to always prepare undercloud images for
containerized underclouds. If built locally with kolla, the undercloud_docker_*
parameters should point to a local registry. If fetched from remote registry,
the same logic applies. Altering `undercloud_docker_*` allows to cover
such cases.

Add the missing `undercloud_docker_registry_tag` parameter. Allow omitting
`undercloud_docker_registry_port`, when a registry host value does not require
a port, like 'docker.io' host.

Closes-bug: #1733800

Change-Id: Ic3d448c8215f44a957711e666a34e78482d8100d
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>
"}]
commit_message:
Fix undercloud containers images prepare

Images for containerized underclouds can be parametrized differently
as for overcloud deployments. For example, undercloud may fetch images
from a promotion pipeline, while overcloud may consume those from the
local registry hosted undercloud.

Align the containerized undercloud case with the recent changes docker registry
host, namespace and tag defaults. Consumed these from the common defaults, yet
allowing to diverge.

Fix conditions for undercloud-deploy to always prepare undercloud images for
containerized underclouds. If built locally with kolla, the undercloud_docker_*
parameters should point to a local registry. If fetched from remote registry,
the same logic applies. Altering `undercloud_docker_*` allows to cover
such cases.

Add the missing `undercloud_docker_registry_tag` parameter. Allow omitting
`undercloud_docker_registry_port`, when a registry host value does not require
a port, like 'docker.io' host.

Closes-bug: #1733800

Change-Id: Ic3d448c8215f44a957711e666a34e78482d8100d
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: I8e769c1dd93bca6a14b6209615f83c09ceceed22

commit_message:
Add ceph_mons to ceph example

The ceph documentation backported to Pike does not include ceph_mons
in the vars example, because the var does not need to be defined in
master.

In Pike however, it does need to be defined, and ceph_client will not
run unless it is defined by the user. Once
Ida44228c2d2919990bac46936317b6093d3ff115 has merged, this commit
can be reverted.

Change-Id: Ia6218dbc90af3e379af28bff5cc957dd3feb81d0

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: I63aeef045ca3804adadfe020d2269b2ee5b11721

commit_message:
Do not check that fernet keys exist on startup

The main reason is that there is no way to check existence of
keys if they are in the backend. The check already happens in
keystone-manage doctor, symptom_keys_in_Fernet_key_repository.

Change-Id: I5d01a823cde29db439161b6fc3f1adb8e5a6e334

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: I0efc7889825a7d5b93f51919b9cc5bc86a1d28e6

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: I700bca2da767f62686013508460c8ceabbb87eb1

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: If5da4725a9c896543f5c7d5212871b9f14afddab

commit_message:
polling: run polling tasks immediately on start

When Ceilometer polling agent start, one has to wait N seconds for the first
polling to happen. This makes testing extremely difficult.

I can't see any good reason to not poll at (re)start. Since the last run time
is lost anyway, the interval will never be perfect. So at least let's make it
convenient by polling on startup.

Also set a default random 0-10 seconds delay before the first poll so if a lot
of daemons are started at the same time they don't all hit the same endpoint at
the same time.

Change-Id: I0741a586cec499c259f0e90977f185c4e68a99d3

commit_message:
Add migration_get_by_uuid in db api.

This will be used by the migration_get_all_by_filters
method which will later be used by the MigrationAPI to
support the migrations pagination.

Part of blueprint add-pagination-and-change-since-for-migration-list

Change-Id: I12c5babaec3a09dd0c6fbb5b77060a352ea373e7

commit_message:
Add instance action record for attach/detach interface

We currently don't record attach/detach interface instance
actions. This is useful for auditing and debuging.

This patch adds attach/detach interface actions.

Change-Id: I0874f52ca7c5e29d9cd619679e1e121b25b6b41e
partial-implements: blueprint fill-the-gap-for-instance-action-records

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: Iad3691cc36b630fdd128d26531ed5dd95eebc0f5

commit_message:
Fix ZUUL_REFNAME

Set up the variables the same way the post job is set up:
Pass them in via environment in job definition.

Pass ZUUL_ environment variables through to jobs.

Note ZUUL_REFNAME is not set, use ZUUL_BRANCH instead.

Change-Id: I5863a05384c9a48445d5ce52ccc508519c7c00f8

commit_message:
Drop journaling related code

This patch is removing the code related to journaling. A new approach
to solve the database consistency problem has been proposed and accepted
at e34e5acf27a86934bbb8ee47e59806c617099870.

The skeleton for migration (and tests) have been kept in the patch
because that will be used later by the new solution.

Change-Id: Id036ca27df6117e8317238bc719ab21f49c431fd

commit_message:
Collect logs to a subfolder

The logs and ara report generated by zuul are
overwriting some of our log content, so this
patch puts our logs into a subfolder instead.

Change-Id: I28712418fb6db4857dc9f74b2ee8b2fbeb651853

commit_message:
Improve lint test flexibility

Currently the ansible-syntax and ansible-lint tests
assume the playbook to be tested against, the role
requirements file location and a single path for all
roles. This patch allows these to be modified so that
the tests can be used for the integrated repo which
does not have the same structure as the roles.

Various lint failures are no being picked up with
these modifications, so they're resolved using quick
hacks.

Change-Id: I8bea90082dbde7de49c5e2e86d298c017b16591d
(cherry picked from commit d861c3902dbda8323a9fa57c72bae720dfedf005)

commit_message:
Collect functional test logs and add logstash index

Currently we don't have functional test logs in the gate which
makes hard to debug failures.

This patch aims to collect logs for those tests in the same
way that Neutron does. It also generates an index file containing
oslo.log messages. This file will then be used to populate logstash
index.

Change-Id: I485425415f5faf01a4ab45ac4ec9aeb78dfeda58
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Create puppet-openstack-guide

Currently Puppet OpenStack documention is hosted on Wiki [1] and we would
like to use RST and Gerrit to manage documentation in future, like other
projects, so we can leave Wiki.

On each existing Wiki page of Puppet OpenStack, we'll give the new URL
so we don't break indexes.

[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Puppet
Change-Id: I8a42fd763913775834c9e621ca7582199705773d

commit_message:
Update the help message for unique_last_password_count

The help message for unique_last_password_count doesn't tell the
count logic to users, so that the users may misunderstand it.

This patch updated the message to make it more clear.

Change-Id: I8ab1db5c07b199a3a0ef86a79e9895be48c0a1db
Closes-bug: #1727099

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: I73558ce52761381a3b61ff50f3394f2f1e50fa8f

commit_message:
Custom formatter

Implements: custom formatter

Custom formatter can be used to output a machine-readable, easily
parsable and customizable format using set of predefined tags
to suite various needs.

Output string is formatted using python string.format() standards
and therefore provides familiar usage.

Usage: bandit --format custom [--msg-template MSG-TEMPLATE] targets

See bandit --help for additional information and list of available tags

modified:   bandit/cli/main.py
modified:   bandit/core/manager.py
modified:   README.rst
modified:   setup.cfg
new file:   bandit/formatters/custom.py

Change-Id: I900c9689cddb048db58608c443305e05e7a4be14
Signed-off-by: Marek Cermak <macermak@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Change template names to queens

The new master branch should point now to queens instead of pike.

So, HOT templates should specify that they might contain features
for queens release [1]

[1]: https://docs.openstack.org/heat/latest/template_guide/hot_spec.html#queens

Change-Id: I7654d1c59db0c4508a9d7045f452612d22493004

WIP Adding octavia-worker configuration settings from post deployment

Instead of configuring some settings in octavia post deployment
script, those configurations will be added to the service resource.

commit_message:
Create variable override tests

This way we ensure in the integrated gates that deployers can
override their variables in userspace.

The bigger interest will come when we upgrade to a new version
of ansible, where the variable behavior could be different.
It then proves we are respecting our contract.

Change-Id: I707b3fd6fdc9e7080d7202f2d70e85f441f5db16

commit_message:
Change perms for the VM logs

When logs were under a directory without read permissions,
bifrost was not able to create the vm log files for centos/suse
and were not published.

Change-Id: Ifcc31c611edd34acb4fc3c1bb67bbe2a528d93cc
(cherry picked from commit 001451bf93eed2dd7bbdd1731124c75cf18a86f7)

commit_message:
Correct minor pike branch config issues

Bifrost has many knobs, and we've not yet made a list
of things that need to be followed-up with each stable
release.

As such, we need to ensure we install the appropriate
stable branch versions from source.

Set the branch, set the IPA image to be the pike image
and change inspector to install from source, as the default
master branch behavior is to use the released version for
testing.

Change-Id: Ia5b63602949db9c11cce3ae40f753b01d59084cc

commit_message:
Set also up-to-date overcloud flavor parameters

Previously we've been setting just the deprecated variants of the
flavor parameters, which could cause problem with custom
role_data.yaml if it didn't include the appropriate
deprecated_param_flavor key for Controller or ObjectStorage roles. Now
we set both the deprecated (for old version support) and the
up-to-date parameter variant (for custom role data).

Change-Id: I53f1a7da3edf4accb9552bb7125e99e468124856
Closes-Bug: #1733327

commit_message:
Improve lint test flexibility

Currently the ansible-syntax and ansible-lint tests
assume the playbook to be tested against, the role
requirements file location and a single path for all
roles. This patch allows these to be modified so that
the tests can be used for the integrated repo which
does not have the same structure as the roles.

Various lint failures are no being picked up with
these modifications, so they're resolved using quick
hacks.

Change-Id: I8bea90082dbde7de49c5e2e86d298c017b16591d

commit_message:
Use common defaults for image prepare CLI

This sources the defaults for the image prepare command from the
common defaults in KollaImageBuilder.

This makes the defaults self-documenting via the --help argument, and
means that only one location needs to be patched downstream if any
defaults change.

Change-Id: Ibc18e6fe84700a6d630b3b03cc1d8de4f75713f2
Closes-Bug: #1727519

commit_message:
Added new parameter: $activate_httplog

This allows to get the full HTTP log (and TCP if not HTTP) from HAProxy,
in case you need any debug from that central point.

In case you want timers for those entries, you might want to use the
already present "$haproxy_globals_override" parameter and set its
content to:
{ 'log' => '/dev/log local0 debug'  }

Change-Id: I4667317cbd453875585521b22b0ccbdb208f5353

commit_message:
docker/internal TLS: spawn extra container for ec2api TLS proxy

This spawns extra containers that runs httpd to run the TLS proxy
that will go in front of ec2-api and ec2-api-metadata.

bp tls-via-certmonger-containers

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-24 11:06:41.000000000', 'message': 'Fix functional and rally tests

This is a squash of the following two inter-dependent changes:
I330588d477a321c51c50a036703ee338dc1933a6
I85fc8c54c0bda4bdfc76f9f74ec40260d998b756

1. Initialize ovn_client properly when mech_driver object is reused

Functional tests currently reuse the mech_driver object and
TestOVNFunctionalBase class calls post_fork_initialize() method.
This forces the IDL connections to be renewed but old ovn_client
object still holds the references to the old connections which
produces NotConnectedError exceptions in ovsdbapp.

This patch fixes it by resetting the ovn_client instance in the
mechanism driver in the post_fork_initialize() method.

2. Add connection row to ovn db

Add connection row to ovn db and change the inactivity_probe
from 5s to 60s.

Change-Id: Ic317bad89d746a1064f1b3591468fc3dd8c8074e
Closes-Bug: #1733399
Co-Authored-By: Dong Jung <dongj@dtdream.com>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Fix functional and rally tests

This is a squash of the following two inter-dependent changes:
I330588d477a321c51c50a036703ee338dc1933a6
I85fc8c54c0bda4bdfc76f9f74ec40260d998b756

1. Initialize ovn_client properly when mech_driver object is reused

Functional tests currently reuse the mech_driver object and
TestOVNFunctionalBase class calls post_fork_initialize() method.
This forces the IDL connections to be renewed but old ovn_client
object still holds the references to the old connections which
produces NotConnectedError exceptions in ovsdbapp.

This patch fixes it by resetting the ovn_client instance in the
mechanism driver in the post_fork_initialize() method.

2. Add connection row to ovn db

Add connection row to ovn db and change the inactivity_probe
from 5s to 60s.

Change-Id: Ic317bad89d746a1064f1b3591468fc3dd8c8074e
Closes-Bug: #1733399
Co-Authored-By: Dong Jung <dongj@dtdream.com>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>

Hi Vinay Kumar,

thanks for the review!

I guess the bottleneck is the parsing required by dnsmasq (and inspector) to process the configuration update. Therefore I guess it's going to be less resource-intense to have to parse just a couple of short files upon a state update. This is possible thanks to the (selective) inotify facility implementation in dnsmasq. Otherwise, considering a + 10k deployment, the dnsmasq (and inspector) would have to perform a lot of parsing of the opts file each time a node got discovered, inspected or phased-out.

Cheers,
milan"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-09-11 12:37:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 56: Verified+1

Hi Vinay Kumar,

thanks for the question!

> Thanks Milan for responding. Makes sense.
> Actually neutron-dhcp is following the model i was refering to.
> Well, so you say the inotify would take care when there is an update in the /etc/dnsmasq.d/ directory.
> I may be missing few points you might have mentioned earlier.
> In the documentation, you mentioned that inotify can not react on delete/update events.

The inotify implementation in dnsmasq doesn't react on file removal or file truncate; best to see is check the source of dnsmasq[1][2] or try manually. I mention that in the docs[3].

> So if a node is deleted how is it handled? Add "ignore" to the whitelisted mac?

Due to the discovery feature[4] it actually has to be white-listed[5] which boils down to removing the ",ignore" directive, if there was one set for a node. It is logically equivalent to an absent file in this particular cache implementation.

Cheers,
milan

[1] https://github.com/aa65535/dnsmasq/blob/master/src/inotify.c#L160
[2] https://github.com/aa65535/dnsmasq/blob/master/src/inotify.c#L180
[3] http://docs-draft.openstack.org/48/466448/56/check/gate-ironic-inspector-docs-ubuntu-xenial/2d21288//doc/build/html/admin/dnsmasq-pxe-filter.html
[4] https://docs.openstack.org/ironic-inspector/latest/user/usage.html#discovery

the dnsmasq service.

Allow to parametrize the hardcoded 'undercloud' domain name.
F.e. RDOcloud uses an 'rdocloud' domain, therefore some DNS things might be

propagate changes to the overcloud/undercloud endpoints' names based on a

commit_message:
Allow to override t-h-t 'Cloud*' params undercloud

Allow to parametrize the hardcoded 'undercloud' domain name.
F.e. RDOcloud uses an 'rdocloud' domain, therefore some DNS things might be
failing with the hardcoded value.
The default domain name remains unchanged. It can be
overriden with a new '--local-domain' option as well.

Related-bug: #1698349
Partial-bug: #1733873

Change-Id: Iad63142b241f9f7f0bbef68473f18b69f36daf76
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Fix glance config generation when using NFS

This commit sets the 'tripleo::glance::nfs_mount::edit_fstab' variable
to false to prevent the glance_api to write to /etc/fstab and fail in
the case we're using an NFS backend.

This also updates the NFS mount option and mount point to align with
the config from the puppet-tripleo module at:

https://github.com/openstack/puppet-tripleo/blob/master/manifests/glance/nfs_mount.pp

Change-Id: Ied27fac67d28b3104441ada469942a19e3c07a89
Closes-Bug: #1732928

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see

commit_message:
Remove setting of version/release from releasenotes

Release notes are version independent, so remove version/release
values. We've found that projects now require the service package
to be installed in order to build release notes, and this is entirely
due to the current convention of pulling in the version information.

Release notes should not need installation in order to build, so this
unnecessary version setting needs to be removed.

This is needed for new release notes publishing, see
I56909152975f731a9d2c21b2825b972195e48ee8 and the discussion starting
at
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-November/124480.html
.

Change-Id: I1c53f58e838e000711261f54dfd9e705e2495e32
